&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ward Sister/ Charge Nurse&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 6&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Permanent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;37.5 hours per week &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen on our busy 25 bedded cardiology ward for a full time ward sister/ charge nurse as we are looking to expand our management team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ward 3a is a 25 bedded medical cardiology ward with capacity to have patient&#39;s on cardiac monitoring that are monitored by the acute cardiac unit. It is a busy and challenging ward and nurses patients with a breadth of different cardiology and medical conditions. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a dynamic, enthusiastic, patient-centred and hard-working individual to join our management to provide leadership and expert knowledge to support our team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;To assist the ward manager in the general running of the ward and to deputise the ward manager in their absence, therefore training on the governance of the ward will be integrated into your training. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ward provides challenges and opportunities that will help you develop your skills and gain further experience. We ensure that you have structured support to be able to achieve your own personal aspirations within the vision of the ward.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are passionate and motivated to further develop your clinical and leadership skills than we would love to hear from you. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Cardiology experience is desirable not essential. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please contact the ward manager, Heather Wright, or ward sister, Michelle Mangan, for any more information on the ward, or to arrange a visit on 0151 706 2335 or email heather.wright@liverpoolft.nhs.uk. We will be happy to explain more about the ward and the model of care. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameHeather WrightJob titleActing Ward ManagerEmail addressheather.wright@liverpoolft.nhs.ukTelephone number0151 706 2333&lt;/p&gt;
